laboratory_examinations.findings: The liver is normal with subcentimeter hypodensities in segment 8 and 7, too small to characterize; the gallbladder is normal; the pancreas is normal; the spleen is normal; kidneys enhance symmetrically with no focal lesions; the appendix is fluid-filled and dilated, measuring up to 9 mm at the tip, indicating early appendicitis; no intraabdominal free air or free fluid.
